 It seems our test didn't cover a specific line, which could be due to the constraints of using JDK 25. I need to reflect on this and consider how we might adjust our approach.\n\n**Rethinking method naming**\n\nI’m considering whether I should update the method name or add a comment to prevent any issues with line coverage. It seems like a smart move to make sure everything stays clear and well-documented. I wonder if it’ll improve readability as well. So, I think that adjusting the method name might be the best next step here to avoid confusion. It’s always good to proactively address potential issues, right?", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_078cdb37dbc42889016a294f780564819089364c3b761188e0\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqKU-rFcv91Y_1hAWZ63phY-bEfnaiAZZImbAlu7B02bZ33bN89QbZiCM4lL5ArtYHs0GWiJOh2zaUgGr3mEapeld_s6nEZZIDfSfLBZ0OM32Q0XiVWODoUDNQcKZoVaJJ4oorftDHBeYtTvs9-1c1Kgk3IowI22Pmxx41I4RWglf-oMKbgcgKm8CS3yNVhsabiPxBH3VNi7qXHlwGi63gnbUu8vcb1QKAksCuQCB_7j5c8IqA8ayZem0wITh4ei7meONbDXVq_pF_eTN7RyCoUCDUy6qBbA16aVigOg6cUDujcL5esaF4NxHfh8mEc2XSMcpPdiGdeH1TacfjmKrfWW29nx1e9iJhoS0hpdrH0wyWxrD7b__AYPfGrsM8qX9dlRo2q7dUFYczkNHJ3SjMc60CVDitOw4tBsxOCpHfuexjR809GfO5m6iJsePLvCtM1MKD8G6Kcy1foM6oGt2_q9n06f4xs8oe2ditpQOUMN82AzdbJaIqpKgzFZcRQs99vUlDQmlwRecBJMEXAh1pKXK2rSi4pf1q7gnizM-Rc62_R9ssg6fv2LGeMH_YI4zL844DeZmbD_EgR8fa2MHhvuw1pAj4bJKWDLFA2VODIW0uYm7G1WqPSHVYbQWzr9Gshd8IISGtSdNZDaTKLkysBTHskjlOYLqLps3R1bZaJXvkIVjKG1icQ3RIZIHA-jRt7woFPbICe0bHKQOzFqyf2sW5K_ysCfnpUyXtxIeGdajhBtnWjVLRtR1JVrPOzB4wxcTwotMLdotjS9Z6Xr-nbwoXyKTsTRyx-Qy3l2JWmsuZl3ILSZW3uHtpyYF9MDyY0rQAXgOjNvTEjHCw_fdL4HixwhKrG-SWpBvF_rB6vyomDj_SByiDin0tU_O-OhzUbSP0BrzrmtkGNzEYEtvOX-_j7cadx4m7CaH7DZ5jdX7IoQW05IVqHDB6wBKTNj9CtiVu-sl58L_xzm3zYZmKuIG_lk76woWALeJ5CZOv_94r3PSgmPfVxUMn1fKJ4MoAwtjd7Sh3a2PXOfsc0qD19JJX9p8x3UedJc1bgBaNEQ2yyNIODFeZSEnw1uUc21DpIXuXgz5SCG9PGdPZd8fGvBzWFpLN-nMUNDIl4efM8XlqF5z1oqkY6-7S5F5znG6DDfPFfoK8OlC_zbo7rqIKqX8i5YKfayq4QmAnzzSewWpAd-oozkzQYeqik06lkjhGACHNI