DK 25's `System.getSecurityManager` returns null, which might be due to an implementation issue. The use of `System.setSecurityManager` raises a UOE, and I can't access certain internals through reflection. I wonder if invoking `Method.invoke` could help if the class method returns a non-null value. Creating a custom `JavaDispatcher` with a non-bootstrap class loader seems impossible due to security restrictions. Using JVM arguments could work, but it feels complex. I think I need to focus on dynamic access coverage for JDK versions below 24.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating code coverage**\\n\\nI'm trying to figure out why previous attempts yielded no coverage. Maybe it’s because the code was modified after the original creation. The user reported that after their second response, \\\"Attempts used 2, no newly covered,\\\" indicating they ran an external test. It seems our test didn't cover a specific line, which could be due to the constraints of using JDK 25. I need to reflect on this and consider how we might adjust our approach.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Rethinking method naming**\\n\\nI’m considering whether I should update the method name or add a comment to prevent any issues with line coverage. It seems like a smart move to make sure everything stays clear and well-documented. I wonder if it’ll improve readability as well. So, I think that adjusting the method name might be the best next step here to avoid confusion. It’s always good to proactively address potential issues, right?\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_rGcoOhTBn8bUqCLWdLauaOzN|fc_078cdb37dbc42889016a294fab9e608190aa4ed5fd6dd1f6bc", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "/tmp/TestSM.java", "content": "public class TestSM { @SuppressWarnings(\"removal\") public static void main(String[] args){ System.out.println(Runtime.version()); System.out.println(System.getProperty(\"java.security.manager\")); try { System.setSecurityManager(new SecurityManager(){ public void checkPermission(java.security.Permission p){} }); System.out.println(System.getSecurityManager()); } catch(Throwable t){ t.printStackTrace(); } }}"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3797, "output": 2280, "cacheRead": 41984, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 48061, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781092214178, "responseId": "resp_078cdb37dbc42889016a294f772678819083060e69bdcde427"}}
